    <header>
        <h1><marquee height="45">Bibimbap</marquee></h1>
    </header>

    <section>
        <h2>Ingredients</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>2 cups cooked short-grain rice</li>
            <li>1 cup julienned carrots, sautéed</li>
            <li>1 cup sliced shiitake mushrooms, sautéed</li>
            <li>1 cup spinach, blanched and seasoned</li>
            <li>1 cup bean sprouts, blanched</li>
            <li>1 cup thinly sliced cucumber</li>
            <li>4 fried eggs</li>
            <li>Sesame oil for drizzling</li>
            <li>Soy sauce for seasoning</li>
            <li>Gochujang (Korean red pepper paste) for serving</li>
            <li>Sesame seeds for garnish</li>
            <li>Chopped green onions for garnish</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Tags</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Bibimbap</li>
            <li>Korean</li>
            <li>Rice</li>
            <li>Veggies</li>
            <li>Eggs</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Instructions</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Divide the cooked rice among serving bowls.</li>
            <li>Arrange the sautéed carrots, mushrooms, seasoned spinach, bean sprouts, and sliced cucumber on top of the rice in a visually appealing manner.</li>
            <li>Place a fried egg on the center of each bowl.</li>
            <li>Drizzle sesame oil over the ingredients and season with soy sauce to taste.</li>
            <li>Serve with a side of gochujang for extra flavor.</li>
            <li>Garnish with sesame seeds and chopped green onions.</li>
            <li>Mix everything together before eating to enjoy the flavors of Bibimbap.</li>
            <li>Enjoy your delicious Bibimbap!</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

